BAFANA Bafana coach Stuart Baxter has expressed his disappointment over the missed opportunity to take part in an international tournament in Thailand. Last month, Safa turned down an invitation from the Football Association of Thailand to play in the annual King’s Cup. Safa was hoping to secure clashes with higher profile teams than the participating nations of Thailand, United Arab Emirates, Gabon and Slovakia, however.But now Bafana will have to settle for a one-day, three nations tournament featuring Zambia and Zimbabwe on the Fifa-sanctioned weekend of 24 March. The mini-tournament will take place in Lusaka. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvFjbiwlI346FY77cpIA35oRGAf4uou6rPWicUDBa1N2bNjrtN-4pmecRsJS9zMv_p2BOWobo4q5YH0N7tmvDIGVnuPqbqzhauaC_C3e2OYJmsxusuFvHeS6AKdFm_NmUeQWCFU4SHjxi15DyQzcpg0M648fyppKbYMLh_Z_SF1RsTA6zl3SPi6Fev8D-a9DVidH0wHNxGZDZ3NsCqaLNViIT8A1dvuGT5SkCqEtcyISX6tQwM1GMFoMkC82oc5ZYpYgeS4gEdzHwDxNI0b\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzKIM7ScmZ-86EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
